{{Reflist|group="g"|refs=
<ref name="DebianSupportPeriod">Debian releases are officially supported for 1 year after the ''subsequent'' release, with releases being approximately 2 years apart. The Debian LTS Project provides community based support extending the complete support period to 5 years.</ref>
<ref name="Tails Releases">All security updates are in new versions which are released every six weeks.</ref>
